  "body": "## Summary\n\nAdd `bedrock_compat` parameter to `ChatAnthropic` to enable compatibility mode for Bedrock proxy and similar proxies that send SSE events without the `event:` field.\n\n## Problem\n\nWhen using `ChatAnthropic` with Bedrock-compatible proxies (or other proxies that do not follow the standard Anthropic SSE format), streaming fails because:\n\n1. Bedrock proxies send SSE events with only `data:` lines\n2. The Anthropic SDK expects both `event:` and `data:` fields\n3. Without the `event:` field, all events are silently skipped, resulting in \"No generation chunks were returned\" error\n\n## Solution\n\nAdd a `bedrock_compat` parameter that, when set to `True`, wraps the streaming response to infer event types from the data payload.\n\n## Usage\n\n```python\nfrom langchain_anthropic import ChatAnthropic\n\nmodel = ChatAnthropic(\n    model=\"anthropic.claude-4-5-opus-20250129\",\n    bedrock_compat=True,\n    base_url=\"https://my-bedrock-proxy.example.com\",\n)\n\nfor chunk in model.stream(\"Hello\"):\n    print(chunk.content, end=\"|\")\n```\n\nFixes #35442",
